<br>
Personally, I play casters and healers well.  I have a nack for knowing when I can cast for max damage without gaining agro in most situations.  I have a nack for knowing when to thrown a heal and which type to maximize my mana usage.  I know many people that play casters and healers as their primary that struggle with these nuances of the game.  I have a melee and can play the melee classes, but as Montyy pointed out, if I stepped into a MT role people would be screaming.  <br>
<br>
Sure it's just a game - but the game mechanics are complex.  If you don't understand the repercussions of an action (for example as a cleric I throw a CH on the MT before he has full agro) you will get yourself and the rest of your group/raid in big trouble. <p><a target= "new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257041"><b>Vonic</b></a>
